The Protomen portion of the story would come from the setting mostly. Semi-modern cyberpunk mega-city surrounded by a wasteland run by a mad scientist dictator who enforces his rule with advanced robots and hired enforcers. The power sources the scientist uses to power his experiments, robots, and to and extent the city itself, is derived from anomalous artifacts that "appear" at semi random intervals in the surrounding wasteland, but will disappear if someone doesn't claim them in a short amount of time, so speed is key. There is an underground rebel group who opposes the mad scientist by attempting to race them to the artifacts first, so they can make a way to counter the dictators robot army, or build their own, but they've been on a losing streak for a while. The main charact is a human pizza delivery driver, who receives an order from one of the members of the underground group, one of the "20 minutes or the pizza is free" deals. The rebels, being street races, think there's no possible way he can make in time on the route he has to take, so free pizza. But somehow, through lucky traffic lights and knowledge of the area, he does, which prompts them to recruit him. The waifur of the story would be either a ferret or a stoat, and act as a mechanic as well as a driver for the rebels
